The above Powershell example will import the PSWindowsUpdate module, run the update installer, and then reboot the PC to apply changes. We should make a point to run updates regularly, especially if we plan to use this host frequently and not destroy it at the end of each engagement. 
Now that we have our updates installed, let us get our package manager and other core tools.

